reviewText: Justo lo que esperaba, me remonto a mi epoca de niez.

Very good Spanish-made, Spanish-language film starring the singing child actress of the 1960's called Marisol.  The story is about a little girl torn between her widowed mother and her paternal grandfather.  I remember seeing it in the theater when I was a child.  On occasion it is shown on a Hispanic movie channel.  I would love to see this movie released in the US on DVD.
